gomodel:SYNGO_4561  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In cultured hippocampal neurons (17 div) transfected with GFP-tagged SNX27 sorting nexin-27 colocalizes with mCherry-PSD95 (Fig. 2A and Fig. 3 upper row) and not with the presynaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig. 2B).\nCo-immunoprecipitation with SNX27-antibody indicates interaction with GluA1 but not with GluA2 AMPA receptors (Fig. 8A).\nSuppl. fig. 2 shows colocalization of epitopes for anti-SNX27 antibody with GFP-SNX27 and mCherry-SNX27 fluorescence.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared from P0 mouse pups\", p. 11\n\nGFP-SNX27 and mCherry SNX27 were generated by subcloning human SNX27 (Origene) into pEGFP-N1 or pmCherry-N1 (Clontech) using Bgl11 and BamH1.\n\nThe source or generation of the antibody for targeting endogenous SNX27 is not described." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4561" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

